{"name":"Disguise","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 36\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 96\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To fashion a facÌ§ade that simulates a particular race/culture/social class, possibly making one appear a few inches taller or shorter and/or several pounds heavier or thinner (cf. the <em>disguise self</em> spell). The assassin also can appear as the opposite sex. This ruse may be accomplished through a combination of acting, makeup, apparel, and perhaps even subtle sorcery. The base chance of the <em>disguise</em> being discerned is 2-in-12, adjusted as the referee deems appropriate. If the assassin has a 16+ charisma, the base chance for being discerned is reduced to 1-in-12.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gxkgVAngDEfiTJd7"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579289023,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"3SFCX6kECRQScXr9","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Harvest Venom","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 97\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To extract venom sacs from snakes, spiders, giant insects, and the like, should the opportunity present and appropriate containers be available. Assassins learn to dissect venomous creatures in the field. This skill is performed at a base 9-in-12 chance of success. If a <em>12</em> is rolled, a mishap occurs, and the assassin is exposed (e.g., eyes, nose, skin) to the poisonous fluid. For more information on the extraction of venom, see <strong>Chapter 9: Combat</strong>, <em>poison, venom harvesting</em>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":9,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gxkgVAngDEfiTJd7"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579289024,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"5V78cZ8zTm27hLMq","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Poison Resistance","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 97\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Toxicological training and exposure to various poisons and toxins provide a +1 bonus on all saving throws versus poison, though not other <em>death</em> saving throws.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gxkgVAngDEfiTJd7"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579289024,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"9YTVfyfiLgxwFitZ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Manipulate Traps","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To find, remove, and reset traps both magical and mundane. Separate checks must be made to accomplish each facet of this skill: <em>find</em>, <em>remove</em>, <em>reset</em>. Failure by more than two, or if a natural <em>12</em> is rolled, may cause the trap to detonate on the thief. Also, a new trap may be built if the mechanism is simple and the parts available; anything more complex requires the assistance of an engineer. Thieves&rsquo; tools are required when practicing this ability.</p>\n<p>Assassins also practice most thievish skills. These abilities progress as the assassin advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":3,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253249264,"modifiedTime":1681579289024,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"E7f8uy6uqSVICdkP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Climb","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To ascend or descend sheer cliffs or walls without need of climbing gear. If vertical, the surface must be rough or cracked. At least one check must be made per 100 feet of climbing. Failure indicates the climber has slipped and fallen at about the midpoint of the check<span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">.</span></p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Assassins also practice most thievish skills. These abilities progress as the assassin advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579289023,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"J33gV6YQ81f5uH9K","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Discern Noise","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To hearken at a door and detect the faintest of noises on the other side, perceive the distant footfalls of a wandering monster, or distinguish a single voice in a crowd. Six rounds (one minute) of concentrated listening are required.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Assassins also practice most thievish skills. These abilities progress as the assassin advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">[</span><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"> -- see </span><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Player's Manual</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">, p.37]</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":4,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.0Z6NzOE7wzNKfkrn"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253207156,"modifiedTime":1681579289023,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"NCPaDQJkKtZBgiFn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Detect Secret Doors","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 36\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 96\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Find a secret door on a base 3-in-6 chance.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"d6","rollType":"below","rollTarget":3,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gxkgVAngDEfiTJd7"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579289023,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"OQXu4a5zHC1geJSE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Open Locks","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To pick locks or disable latching mechanisms both magical and mundane. Thieves&rsquo; tools are required. Picking or dismantling a lock may be attempted but once; if the attempt fails, the assassin cannot try again until he has gained a level of experience. Most locks require 1d4 minutes to pick; complex locks might necessitate 3d6 minutes.</p>\n<p>Assassins also practice most thievish skills. These abilities progress as the assassin advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":3,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253307994,"modifiedTime":1681579289024,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"U32lI37JFJAFhB7v","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Extraordinary Dexterity","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 27\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>+8% chance to perform <em>extraordinary feats of dexterity</em> (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>dexterity</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"d100","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.MU9Ad6GulTFsmkIb"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679249969686,"modifiedTime":1681579289024,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"afT3lCVCqbJdh5fk","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Agile","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 36\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>+1 AC bonus when unarmoured and unencumbered (shield allowed).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579289022,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"gxkgVAngDEfiTJd7","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Assassinate (Backstab)","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 96\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>A backstab (cf. the thief ability) attempt made with a class 1 or 2 melee weapon, with the intent to <em>assassinate</em>. The target must be unaware of attack, which may be the result of <em>hiding</em> or <em>moving silently</em>. Also, the target must have vital organs (e.g., <strong>skeleton</strong>, <strong>zombie</strong> exempt) and a discernible &ldquo;back&rdquo; (e.g., <strong>green slime</strong>, <strong>purple worm</strong> exempt). If the requirements are met, the following benefits are derived:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">The attack roll is made at +4 &ldquo;to hit.&rdquo;</span></li>\n<li>If target is hit, a second d20 is rolled to verify <em>assassination</em> (see <strong>Table 56</strong>).</li>\n<li>If the second d20 roll meets the required target number or less, the target must make a <em>death</em> saving throw or die; however, if the original d20 attack roll was a natural <em>19</em> or <em>20</em>, then no saving throw is allowed.</li>\n<li>Normal <em>backstab</em> damage rules per the thief class apply if the result is a hit but not an automatic <em>assassination</em>. Additional damage dice are rolled according to the assassin&rsquo;s level of experience:\n<ul>\n<li>1st to 4th levels = &times;2</li>\n<li>5th to 8th levels = &times;3</li>\n<li>9th to 12th levels = &times;4</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Other damage modifiers (strength, sorcery, etc.) are added afterwards (e.g., a 5th-level assassin with 13 strength and a <strong>+1 short sword</strong> rolls 3d6+2).</li>\n<li>Note that if an <em>assassination</em> attempt is made against an assassin of higher level, the chance-in-twenty of success is reduced by one for every level of difference.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Sniper Attack</strong>: Lastly, unlike the thief&rsquo;s <em>backstab</em> ability, the assassin also can make an <em>assassination</em> attempt with a missile weapon (such as a bow or thrown dagger) versus a human, humanoid, quasi-man, or giant. The attempt requires short range; the mark must be completely unaware of danger and not otherwise engaged in combat. The assassin&rsquo;s comprehensive knowledge of anthropoid anatomy allows for this specialized termination attempt.</p>\n<p>[<strong>Table 56: Assassination</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.95]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gxkgVAngDEfiTJd7"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579289023,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"h6qDbBwSVR6km0tK","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Hide","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To vanish into shadows, camouflage oneself, or flatten one&rsquo;s body to a seemingly impossible degree&mdash;all whilst remaining still as a statue. Only the slightest movement is permissible (e.g., unsheathing a blade, opening a pouch). Hiding is impossible in direct sunlight, or if the assassin is observed.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Assassins also practice most thievish skills. These abilities progress as the assassin advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":5,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YmH1P6aCQAG3Z5FM"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253228973,"modifiedTime":1681579289024,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"oEFKDdREW2k8NZ1D","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Poison Use","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 97\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 97\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>The employment of toxins to kill or assassinate. Some assassins&rsquo; guilds have in-house alchemists who concoct poisons and toxins potentially available for purchase. Consult your referee regarding availability.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gxkgVAngDEfiTJd7"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579289024,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"sRWpMOLSNP1Fhecg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Move Silently","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To move with preternatural quiet, even across squeaky floorboards, dry leaves, loose debris, and the like. This skill is executed at half the assassin's normal movement rate.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Assassins also practice most thievish skills. These abilities progress as the assassin advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">[</span><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"> -- see </span><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Player's Manual</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">, p.37]</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":5,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.uzHGdCAvDZiVKAx1"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253287286,"modifiedTime":1681579289024,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"xLlwL7BFacZWLHPW","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Poison Manufacture","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 97\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 97\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 97\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 9th level, eligible to train with a master alchemist/ toxicologist and learn how to concoct debilitating and deadly poisons. See <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <em>alchemy</em> for more information.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"assassin 9","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gxkgVAngDEfiTJd7"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579289024,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"zXlw1NSqrBEkJxOp","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
